MOLETLANE cops near Zebediela, Limpopo, have arrested a 36-year-old woman for allegedly stabbing her twin sister to death. The incident took place on Wednesday, 18 January, in Ga-Mogotlane village. Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the suspect was arrested on Friday, 20 January, after being on the run. He added that the police were called to a scene of domestic violence and upon arrival, found a woman lying in a pool of blood with multiple stab wounds.  “The victim was certified dead on the scene. A case of murder was opened, and preliminarily investigation revealed that the victim got into a heated argument with her twin sister, who then fetched a knife and stabbed her several times. The suspect further chopped the sister with an axe before fleeing the scene,” Mojapelo said. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments She was tracked down and arrested while hiding at her boyfriend’s house in a nearby village. She will appear in the Moletlane Periodical Court on Monday, 23 January, facing a charge of murder.